.TH "HTMLIMAGEELEMENT.WIDTH" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLImageElement.width \- HTMLImageElement: width property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]width\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R] interface indicates the width at which the
image is drawn, in CSS pixels, if the image is being drawn or rendered
to any visual medium such as a screen or printer.
Otherwise, it\(cqs the natural, pixel density\-corrected width of the
image.
.SH VALUE
An integer value indicating the width of the image.
The way the width is defined depends on whether the image is being
rendered to a visual medium or not.
.IP \(bu 2
If the image is being rendered to a visual medium such as a screen or
printer, the width is expressed in CSS pixels.
.IP \(bu 2
Otherwise, the image\(cqs width is represented using its natural
(intrinsic) width, adjusted for the display density as indicated by
\f[CR]naturalWidth\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
In this example, two different sizes are provided for an image of a
clock using the \f[CR]srcset\f[R] attribute.
One is 200px wide and the other is 400px wide.
Further, the \f[CR]sizes\f[R] attribute is provided to specify the width
at which the image should be drawn given the viewport\(cqs width.
.SS HTML
For viewports up to 400px wide, the image is drawn at a width of 200px.
Otherwise, it\(cqs drawn at 400px.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]p\f[R]>Image width: <\f[B]span\f[R] class=\(dqsize\(dq>?</\f[B]span\f[R]>px (resize to update)</\f[B]p\f[R]>
<\f[B]img\f[R]
  src=\(dq/en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-200px.png\(dq
  alt=\(dqClock\(dq
  srcset=\(dq
    /en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-200px.png 200w,
    /en\-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/img/clock\-demo\-400px.png 400w
  \(dq
  sizes=\(dq(width \f[B]<\f[R]= 400px) 200px, 400px\(dq />
.EE
.SS JavaScript
The JavaScript code looks at the \f[CR]height\f[R] to determine the
height of the image given the width at which it\(cqs currently drawn.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] clockImage = document.querySelector(\(dqimg\(dq);
\f[B]let\f[R] output = document.querySelector(\(dq.size\(dq);

\f[B]const\f[R] updateWidth = () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  output.innerText = clockImage.width;
};

updateWidth();
window.addEventListener(\(dqresize\(dq, updateWidth);
.EE
.SS Result
This example may be easier to try out in its own window.
